description:
Update the existing providers/CLAUDE.md to document the ProviderError pattern used by all new BD providers.

Add to Critical Rules:
- All provider functions throw ProviderError on failure (not raw HTTP/SDK errors)
- ProviderError shape: { provider: string, operation: string, statusCode: number, rawResponse: unknown }
- Feature layer catches ProviderError and maps to throwError() codes
- Never let raw AWS/Upload-Post/Whisper errors leak to the feature layer

Add to Recipe section:
```typescript
class ProviderError extends Error {
  constructor(
    public provider: string,
    public operation: string,
    public statusCode: number,
    public rawResponse: unknown,
  ) { super(`${provider}.${operation} failed (${statusCode})`) }
}
```

MODIFY: providers/CLAUDE.md

ACCEPTANCE:
- ProviderError pattern documented
- All 4 new providers reference it
- Existing providers (email, payments, content) unaffected

Write landing page integration tests with specific assertions.

WHAT: Create features/(life)/landing/landing.test.ts.

WHY: 100% test coverage rule. Verify all sections render, CTAs work, A/B variants function.

SPECIFIC TESTS:

```ts
import { describe, test, expect } from 'bun:test'
import app from '@/platform/server/app'

describe('Landing Page', () => {
  test('GET / returns 200 with text/html content type', async () => {
    const res = await app.fetch(new Request('http://localhost/'))
    expect(res.status).toBe(200)
    expect(res.headers.get('content-type')).toContain('text/html')
  })

  test('HTML contains DOCTYPE and complete structure', async () => {
    const res = await app.fetch(new Request('http://localhost/'))
    const html = await res.text()
    expect(html).toStartWith('<!DOCTYPE html>')
    expect(html).toContain('<main')
    expect(html).toContain('</main>')
  })

  test('contains all section content', async () => {
    const res = await app.fetch(new Request('http://localhost/'))
    const html = await res.text()
    // Hero
    expect(html).toContain('transforms your life')
    // Problem
    expect(html).toContain("You've done the work")
    // Mechanism
    expect(html).toContain('See Clearly')
    // Transformation
    expect(html).toContain('Imagine it')
    // Curriculum
    expect(html).toContain('The Wake-Up Call')
    // Offer
    expect(html).toContain('$197/year')
    // FAQ
    expect(html).toContain('How long does the course take')
  })

  test('contains CTA link to checkout redirect', async () => {
    const res = await app.fetch(new Request('http://localhost/'))
    const html = await res.text()
    expect(html).toContain('/api/checkout/redirect')
  })

  test('variant B renders correct headline', async () => {
    const res = await app.fetch(new Request('http://localhost/?v=b'))
    const html = await res.text()
    expect(html).toContain("You already know what to do")
  })

  test('sets lp_variant cookie', async () => {
    const res = await app.fetch(new Request('http://localhost/?v=c'))
    const cookie = res.headers.get('set-cookie')
    expect(cookie).toContain('lp_variant=c')
  })

  test('cookie persists variant across requests', async () => {
    const res1 = await app.fetch(new Request('http://localhost/?v=d'))
    const cookie = res1.headers.get('set-cookie')?.split(';')[0] || ''
    const res2 = await app.fetch(new Request('http://localhost/', {
      headers: { cookie }
    }))
    const html = await res2.text()
    expect(html).toContain("You don't need another course")
  })

  test('includes Google Fonts and styles.css', async () => {
    const res = await app.fetch(new Request('http://localhost/'))
    const html = await res.text()
    expect(html).toContain('fonts.googleapis.com')
    expect(html).toContain('/styles.css')
  })

  test('includes meta description', async () => {
    const res = await app.fetch(new Request('http://localhost/'))
    const html = await res.text()
    expect(html).toContain('meta name="description"')
  })
})
```

